{"id":214,"date":"2017-02-12T08:54:11","date_gmt":"2017-02-12T08:54:11","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/?p=214"},"modified":"2018-02-01T23:24:44","modified_gmt":"2018-02-01T23:24:44","slug":"tax-rates","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/tax-rates\/","title":{"rendered":"Tax Rates"},"content":{"rendered":"<h4><strong>Create new tax<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Perfex CRM gives you the ability to add unlimited tax rates on your invoices\/estimates\/proposals etc..<\/p>\n<p>You can add new tax rates by\u00a0followig the steps below:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>Navigate to Setup-&gt;Finance-&gt;Tax Rates.<\/li>\n<li>Click on the top left button <strong>New Tax<\/strong><\/li>\n<li>Enter tax name<\/li>\n<li>Enter tax rate<\/li>\n<li>Click Save<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<p>The tax you created will be available in the dropdown for each item.<\/p>\n<div class=\"st-alert st-alert-info \">When updating tax and this tax is already applied on item the tax information wont be changed.<\/div>\n<h4><strong>Hide tax per item<\/strong><\/h4>\n<p>Perfex CRM by default shows tax per item, there is option to turn this off and all the taxes will be calculated on the bottom of the invoice\/estimate.<\/p>\n<p>Note that when you add your invoice\/estimate items <strong>you will still need to add the item taxes<\/strong> to get the desired calculations. The tax per item will be hidden when your customer view the invoice\/estimate.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-127\" src=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"948\" height=\"253\" srcset=\"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item.png 948w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item-300x80.png 300w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item-768x205.png 768w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item-60x16.png 60w, https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2017\/02\/tax-per-item-150x40.png 150w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 948px) 100vw, 948px\" \/><\/p>\n<p>To disable this feature navigate to<strong> Setup-&gt;Settings-&gt;Finance<\/strong> and set\u00a0<strong>Show TAX per item (Invoices\/Estimates)<\/strong> to <strong>NO<\/strong>.<\/p>\n<p><strong>NOTE<\/strong>: If you are using your own templates for generating PDF for estimates and invoices you should not remove this logic from the templates if you want this option to work as it should, otherwise you can adjust the template to fit to your needs no matter how Show TAX per item option is set.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Create new tax Perfex CRM gives you the ability to add unlimited tax rates on your invoices\/estimates\/proposals etc.. You can add new tax rates by\u00a0followig the steps below: Navigate to Setup-&gt;Finance-&gt;Tax Rates. Click on the top left button New Tax Enter tax name Enter tax rate Click Save The tax you created will be available [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"footnotes":""},"categories":[31,20,16],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-214","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","hentry","category-setup-and-configuration","category-general","category-sales"],"aioseo_notices":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/214","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/help.perfexcrm.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=214"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"hre